{
  "stem": "23942.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We had to carry it from, from the oven, from the communal oven.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Because there was an oven that there was no other-- that everybody could put the cholent in there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And that was so peaceful, after you came from shul.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And it was beautiful and peaceful and nice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And the Jewish people, were-- they knew-- the goyim knew, the non-Jews knew that Jews observe Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They knew.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "There was even a Shabbos goy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "If you needed somebody to light-- if something went wrong, there were certain people knew that they have to do something for the, you know, that Jewish people didn't do.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And that's the way it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And, and, and, and there was, was-- there was rest and reading.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And the women, those that read, that sat around and read-- and sat around those that liked to read, non-- besides read other things, like Shalom Aleichem, on some of the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And it was-- it was so beautiful that I would give anything to, to get just one day back.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- we-- we-- I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah, I would sometimes walk with my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I would walk by myself a half an hour, 20 minutes, I don't remember exactly how long.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I knew my way.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I didn't have to be afraid that a car is going to run me over.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were no cars then, hardly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You never saw a car.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The only-- and-- and even the horse and wagon went at a pace that you weren't afraid of.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "If a man was sitting on a wagon, he would-- you know, I would walk on the side, and nothing happened.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I could walk, and nobody would ever kidnap me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was never afraid of kidnapping.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
